Package: reef
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, fish (>= 3.0), bash
Description: Bash compatibility layer for fish shell
 Reef makes bash syntax work seamlessly inside fish shell. No prefix commands,
 no mode switching, no learning curve. You type bash — fish runs it.
 .
 Includes detection, AST translation, and bash passthrough with environment
 diffing. 498 tests, zero dependencies, ~490KB binary.

Package: reef-tools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, fish (>= 3.0)
Recommends: ripgrep, fd-find, sd, dust, procs, eza, bat, zoxide
Description: Modern CLI tool wrappers for fish — grep→rg, find→fd, cat→bat
 Drop-in replacements that swap legacy coreutils for faster, modern
 alternatives. Each wrapper fully mimics the original tool's flag interface,
 translating GNU flags to their modern equivalents.
 .
 Wrappers for tools you haven't installed simply pass through to the original.
